I no longer do here.
I believe in micro-lending, but Kiva has betrayed my trust and that of other lenders. Some loans will go sour, but when they do we should be told why, to the best of Kiva's ability.
Instead, Kiva blows smoke about how awesome lenders are, about how awesome Kiva is, about how awesome its lending partners are, and about how awesome its borrowers are.
When they finally admitted that things had gone wrong, they said “We hope that you realize that this default is a true exception to the norm and that you will give lending to the working poor another chance on our site.” But my problem isn't with the working poor (nor with the poor who cannot find work); my problem is with Kiva.
